title.narrative: Cross sectorial for multiple outcomes (health, Education, Child Protection) in the refugees camps Tindouf

description.narrative: UNICEF pursued the implementation of the three-year strategy for its humanitarian intervention in Tindouf which has five major objectives on immunization, neonatal and maternal care, education, youth and child rights' promotion in the five refugee camps. Progresses has been achieved in the access of children to quality education, in the area of mothers and children's health, of care and education of children living with disability, in the reinforcement of adolescents' life skills and of advocacy for child rights implementation. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:29/12/2019
